---
import { Plus, Minus } from 'lucide-react';
---

<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12 sm:mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 sm:mb-6">
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Get answers to common questions about GIS implementation, facilities mapping, and our spatial technology services
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Items -->
    <div class="space-y-4 sm:space-y-6">
      <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-6 sm:p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-6 sm:pr-8">
              What is GIS and how can it benefit my organization?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-5 sm:w-6 h-5 sm:h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 pb-6 sm:pb-8" style="display: none;">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed text-sm sm:text-base">
            GIS (Geographic Information System) is a technology that captures, stores, analyzes, and visualizes 
            spatial data. It helps organizations make better decisions by revealing patterns, relationships, 
            and trends in location-based data, improving operational efficiency by 30-40%.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-6 sm:p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-6 sm:pr-8">
              How long does a typical GIS implementation take?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-5 sm:w-6 h-5 sm:h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 pb-6 sm:pb-8" style="display: none;">
          <div class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed space-y-2 sm:space-y-3 text-sm sm:text-base">
            <p>Implementation timelines vary based on complexity: Simple facility mapping projects take 6-8 weeks, 
            while comprehensive enterprise GIS systems require 12-16 weeks.</p>
            <p>The process includes discovery, system design, development, testing, deployment, and user training 
            with regular milestone reviews and client feedback sessions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-6 sm:p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-6 sm:pr-8">
              Can GIS integrate with our existing software systems?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-5 sm:w-6 h-5 sm:h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 pb-6 sm:pb-8" style="display: none;">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed text-sm sm:text-base">
            Yes, our GIS solutions integrate seamlessly with existing systems through REST APIs, web services, 
            and custom connectors. We support integration with ERP systems (SAP, Oracle), facility management 
            software, IoT platforms, and databases to create a unified spatial data ecosystem.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-6 sm:p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-6 sm:pr-8">
              What types of data can be mapped in a GIS system?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-5 sm:w-6 h-5 sm:h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 pb-6 sm:pb-8" style="display: none;">
          <div class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed space-y-2 sm:space-y-3 text-sm sm:text-base">
            <p>GIS can map virtually any data with location components: building assets, equipment, utilities, 
            environmental sensors, personnel, vehicles, infrastructure, land parcels, and natural features.</p>
            <p>Real-time data from IoT sensors, GPS devices, and external APIs can be continuously updated 
            to provide live operational dashboards and monitoring capabilities.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-6 sm:p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-6 sm:pr-8">
              Is GIS suitable for both indoor and outdoor facility mapping?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-5 sm:w-6 h-5 sm:h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 pb-6 sm:pb-8" style="display: none;">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed text-sm sm:text-base">
            Absolutely. Our GIS solutions handle both indoor and outdoor mapping with seamless integration. 
            Indoor mapping includes floor plans, room assignments, equipment locations, and wayfinding, 
            while outdoor mapping covers site layouts, utilities, parking, and landscape features.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-6 sm:p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-6 sm:pr-8">
              What ongoing support and maintenance do you provide?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-5 sm:w-6 h-5 sm:h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 pb-6 sm:pb-8" style="display: none;">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed text-sm sm:text-base">
            We provide comprehensive support including 24/7 system monitoring, regular updates, user training, 
            technical support, data backup management, and system optimization. Our support packages include 
            remote assistance, on-site visits when needed, and continuous system improvement recommendations.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Item 7 -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="w-full text-left p-6 sm:p-8 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:bg-gray-50">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 pr-6 sm:pr-8">
              Can the GIS system work offline for field operations?
            </h3>
            <Plus className="w-5 sm:w-6 h-5 sm:h-6 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" />
          </div>
        </button>
        <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 pb-6 sm:pb-8" style="display: none;">
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed text-sm sm:text-base">
            Yes, our mobile GIS applications support full offline functionality. Field workers can access maps, 
            collect data, and perform analysis without internet connectivity. All offline data automatically 
            syncs when connection is restored, ensuring no data loss and continuous productivity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="text-center mt-12 sm:mt-16">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary to-cyan-500 text-white p-6 sm:p-8 rounded-2xl">
        <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold mb-3 sm:mb-4">Ready to Transform Your Spatial Data?</h3>
        <p class="text-blue-100 mb-4 sm:mb-6 text-sm sm:text-base">Our GIS experts are ready to create powerful mapping solutions for your organization</p>
        <a href="/contact?#contact-form" class="bg-white text-blue-600 font-semibold px-6 sm:px-8 py-3 rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors duration-300 inline-block text-sm sm:text-base">
          Start Your Project
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  // Add FAQ toggle functionality
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
    const faqButtons = document.querySelectorAll('section button');
    
    faqButtons.forEach(button => {
      button.addEventListener('click', function(this: HTMLButtonElement) {
        const content = this.nextElementSibling as HTMLElement;
        const icon = this.querySelector('svg') as SVGElement;
        
        if (content.style.display === 'none' || content.style.display === '') {
          content.style.display = 'block';
          icon.classList.remove('lucide-plus');
          icon.classList.add('lucide-minus');
        } else {
          content.style.display = 'none';
          icon.classList.remove('lucide-minus');
          icon.classList.add('lucide-plus');
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>